<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="../../w/index-title=Sailing_(Christopher_Cross_song)&action=edit&section=1.php.html" title="Edit section: In popular culture">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="In_popular_culture">In popular culture</span></h2>
<p>The Mexican airline <a href="AeroM%C3%A9xico" title="AeroMéxico" class="mw-redirect">AeroMéxico</a> used the theme during the middle 1980s as a jingle for its advertisements; it was also used for the <a href="Cigarette" title="Cigarette">cigarette</a> brand <a href="Winston_(cigarette)" title="Winston (cigarette)">Winston</a>.</p>
<p>"Sailing" has been sampled in several other songs, including <a href="Puff_Daddy" title="Puff Daddy" class="mw-redirect">Puff Daddy</a>'s "<a href="Forever_(Puff_Daddy_album)" title="Forever (Puff Daddy album)">Best Friend</a>" (1999) and <a href="Bone_Thugs-n-Harmony" title="Bone Thugs-n-Harmony">Bone Thugs-n-Harmony</a>'s "<a href="Behind_the_Harmony" title="Behind the Harmony">Paradise</a>" (2006), and <a href="Chris_Brown_(American_entertainer)" title="Chris Brown (American entertainer)">Chris Brown</a>'s "Can't Let You Go." <a href="../Dr._Octagon" title="Dr. Octagon">Dr. Octagon</a>'s song "<a href="../Dr._Octagonecologyst" title="Dr. Octagonecologyst">Blue Flowers Revisited</a>" (1996) contains a brief interpolation of the chorus.</p>
